The paper deals with a problem of optimal decision-making under uncertainty, which is a common theme in several subfields of computer science. The use of probability distributions and the concept of a prophet suggest that the paper may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) or game theory (cs.GT) subcategories. The focus on algorithms and the use of a single set of samples suggest that the paper may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG) subcategories. Finally, the mention of mechanism design suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategory.
